answer: The primary figure from "AN EVALUATION OF UNCONDITIONAL 3D MOLECULAR" (arXiv:2505.00518) compares the distributions of drug-likeness metrics, indicating convergence to the GEOM Drugs space, which represents the DrugBank domain of approved drugs. High QED values (QED > 0.8) for these reference molecules are used as a proxy for drug-likeness.
ground_truth: GEOM Drugs less concentrated at QED > 0.8 than DrugBank
